title: Regional Action Plan for Sustainable Consumption and Production in the Mediterranean
abstract: The SCP Regional Action Plan addresses key human activities which have an impact on the Mediterranean marine and coastal environment. It defines common objectives and identifies actions guiding the implementation of SCP in four priority areas namely Food, fisheries and agriculture; Goods manufacturing; Tourism and Housing and construction.

title: Regional Action Plan for Sustainable Consumption and Production in the Mediterranean
abstract: The SCP Regional Action Plan addresses key human activities which have an impact on the Mediterranean marine and coastal environment. It defines common objectives and identifies actions guiding the implementation of SCP in four priority areas namely Food, fisheries and agriculture; Goods manufacturing; Tourism and Housing and construction.

title: The set of regional policy measures to support green and circular businesses in the Mediterranean
abstract: The measures, adopted by Mediterranean countries during COP22 of the Barcelona Convention, will contribute to the transition towards a circular, green and blue economy in the region.

title: The set of regional policy measures to support green and circular businesses in the Mediterranean
abstract: The measures, adopted by Mediterranean countries during COP22 of the Barcelona Convention, will contribute to the transition towards a circular, green and blue economy in the region.

title: Open Eco-Innovation manual for Circular Economy enablers
abstract: The objective of this document is to develop an open ecoinnovation manual to help match companies and public institutions in search of green and circular business solutions with entrepreneur providers using an open innovation approach.

title: Circular Business Opportunities in the South Mediterranean: How Can Businesses Lead the Way to Sustainable Fashion?
abstract: This publication focuses on the different strategies to help achieve a transition to circular economy in the south Mediterranean textile and fashion industry.

title: Guidelines to tackle single-use plastic products in the Mediterranean region
abstract: The guidelines target policy-makers and provide them with a step-by-step approach for developing the most appropriate framework to prevent the negative impacts of single-use plastic products, including marine litter generation. T

title: Guidelines to address single-use plastics through public procurement in the Mediterranean
abstract: The guidelines target policy-makers in the Contracting Parties to the Barcelona Convention and provide them with a step-by-step approach for developing the appropriate framework to address the reduction of single-use plastics through procurement in the public sector.

title: Guidelines to phase out single-use plastic bags in the Mediterranean
abstract: The guidelines intend to provide a common understanding of the set of measures that can be considered in developing the most appropriate legal and regulatory framework to introduce the non-single use of plastic bags in the signatory countries of the Barcelona Convention.

title: Guidelines to phase out single-use plastic bags in the Mediterranean
abstract: The guidelines intend to provide a common understanding of the set of measures that can be considered in developing the most appropriate legal and regulatory framework to introduce the non-single use of plastic bags in the signatory countries of the Barcelona Convention.

title: Circular Economy Business Strategies: Conceptual Framework to Guide the Development of Sustainable Business Models
abstract: In this article, we set out a framework for circular economy business strategies. We argue that the shift to sustainable patterns of consumption and production that is urgently needed can be enabled only by pursuing a set of sustainable business models. We also propose a definition of a sustainable business model and show how value creation happens. Finally, we also suggest a hierarchy among the business models based on retention of value and extension of responsibility.

title: A Circular Blue Economy for the Mediterranean: current practices and opportunities
abstract: The overall aim of this report is to describe the state of play in the development of circular economy in Selected sectors of the Blue Economy in the Mediterranean. It is the result of a joint work with the Blue Growth Community and the SwitchMed prorgamme.
